        "client_msg_id": "e8c71f5e-1584-45b1-b08e-c1b50ba1a6bf",
        "text": "Help!  I find Discord to be nearly unusable, yet so many dev tool companies use it as a primary interface for their communities.  I have two questions for this community:\n1. Can anyone here offer me tips on how to interact with Discord in a way that doesn’t feel so dreadful (it currently feels impossible to stay up to date on all the discussions and just as difficult to try to catch up)?\n2. If you were starting a community for a dev tool today what technologies\/approach would you take?  (The feeling you are trying to create is, inclusive, welcoming, rich with information.  Kind of like a mix between beautiful library that welcomes readers of all skill level and holds seemingly magical archives with works that only true experts would seek out, and a portion of a public part where you know you can reliably hang out and hear what the scene is talking about.)\nThank you in advance for your suggestions which will surely be better than the impulses I feel to grab a dull spoon and aggressively antagonize my eyeballs every time I am on Discord for more than 5 minutes.",
        "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
        "user_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
