                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "Help!  I find Discord to be nearly "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "unusable, yet",
                                "style": {
                                    "unlink": true
                                }
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": " so many dev tool companies use it as a primary interface for their communities.  I have two questions for this community:\n"
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "rich_text_list",
                        "elements": [
                            {
                                "type": "rich_text_section",
                                "elements": [
                                    {
                                        "type": "text",
                                        "text": "Can anyone here offer me tips on how to interact with Discord in a way that doesn’t feel so dreadful (it currently feels impossible to stay up to date on all the discussions and just as difficult to try to catch up)?"
                                    }
                                ]
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "rich_text_section",
                                "elements": [
                                    {
                                        "type": "text",
                                        "text": "If you were starting a community for a dev tool today what technologies\/approach would you take?  (The feeling you are trying to create is, inclusive, welcoming, rich with information.  Kind of like a mix between beautiful library that welcomes readers of all skill level and holds seemingly magical archives with works that only true experts would seek out, and a portion of a public part where you know you can reliably hang out and hear what the scene is talking about.)"
                                    }
                                ]
                            }
                        ],
                        "style": "ordered",
                        "indent": 0,
                        "border": 0
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "rich_text_section",
                        "elements": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "Thank you in advance for your suggestions which will surely be better than the impulses I feel to grab a dull spoon and aggressively antagonize my eyeballs every time I am on Discord for more than 5 minutes."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
