        "client_msg_id": "6e7b674f-faa7-45a3-b6f3-23ac2b4504d5",
        "text": "I find getting\/keeping on top of all discussions is more a problem of raw volume than the software. Small discord servers are easy to keep up on. With large ones, like most popular community servers, I don't bother trying, and instead pick a few channels to focus on. But that was true old-school forums, too. I recommend disabling most notifications.\n\nFor a new community, I don't know, maybe one of the nice XMPP servers. That's more viable than average for a tech community in particular. They're trying to make it happen again. <https:\/\/xmpp.org\/software\/?category=servers&amp;cscore=advanced&amp;csim=advanced&amp;csmobile=advanced&amp;csweb=advanced&amp;csav=core|https:\/\/xmpp.org\/software\/?category=servers&amp;cscore=advanced&amp;csim=advanced&amp;csmobile=advanced&amp;csweb=advanced&amp;csav=core> I remember hearing good things about Prosody as a relatively turn-key setup, but ejabberd is obviously one of the classics. Someday I'll test-drive a couple of them..m",
